{
  "texts": [
    "Flow Matching for Per-Token Prediction To model per-token conditional distributions in continuous latent space, ENMA employs Flow Matching (FM).",
    "i ∈ R d denote the ground-truth latent token at position i in the frame Z L = (z L 1,.",
    ", z L M), and let zL i be its contextual embedding produced by the spatial transformer.",
    "We drop the superscripts for clarity here.",
    "We seek to learn the conditional distribution p(z | z) via a flow-based transport from a base distribution p 0 = N (0, I) to the target p 1 = p(z | z)."
  ]
}